in giant all-caps letters, was =E2=80=9CCountry First.=E2=80=9D Dana and I =
both chuckled. The two of us were on John McCain=E2=80=99s campaign bus bac=
k in 2008, when that was McCain=E2=80=99s slogan, a cudgel deployed by the =
Vietnam War hero against his liberal, antiwar opponent, Barack Obama.

Republicans, after all, are usually the ones wrapping themselves in the Ame=
rican flag. But now it=E2=80=99s Kamala Harris, the newly ordained Democrat=
ic nominee, who=E2=80=99s running
as the tough patriot. In her telling, it=E2=80=99s Donald Trump who would r=
oll back our freedoms, cater to dictators, and undermine the Constitution. =
=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=9CAs president, I will never waver in defense of A=
merica=E2=80=99s security and ideals, because in the enduring struggle betw=
een democracy and tyranny, I know where I stand and I know where the United=
 States belongs,=E2=80=9D Harris declared in her address on Thursday night.=
 =E2=80=9CFellow Americans,=E2=80=9D she continued, =E2=80=9CI love our cou=
ntry with all my heart.=E2=80=9D

Yes, this was a Democrat talking. There were paeans to diversity and plural=
ism, of course, vows to protect abortion rights and stand up to big corpora=
tions. But Harris, and the many speakers in both parties who came before he=
r, also promised to maintain the =E2=80=9Cmost lethal=E2=80=9D military on =
Earth, to shore up the broken U.S.-Mexico border, and to protect the merito=
cratic American dream. Unlike 2020, when she stumbled through a Democratic =
primary in which everyone was racing
to the left, Harris=E2=80=99s audience last week was not Bushwick or Burlin=
gton. It was the suburban middle. The deciders.

Harris campaign strategists, very much aware that plenty of voters still th=
ink the Democratic nominee is too liberal, are trying to bury those concern=
s, and unabashedly playing to win. Harris=E2=80=99s flip-flops on issues sh=
e once supported=E2=80=94Medicare for All, abolishing I.C.E., banning frack=
ing=E2=80=94are absolutely brazen. And so far, Democrats don=E2=80=99t seem=
 to care. Independents don=E2=80=99t seem to, either, according to polls. A=
nd party insiders who are sick of genuflecting to the left? They=E2=80=99re=
