           <p style=3D"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 30px; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0;">Happy Monday, and welcome b=
ack to The Best &amp; The Brightest. I=E2=80=99m <b>Peter</b> <b>Hamby</b>.=
 <br/><br/>Like a lot of people who went to the Democratic National Convent=
ion last week, I=E2=80=99ve finally made it back home and am desperately tr=
ying to catch up on lost sleep. <br/><br/>Tonight, details from our new pos=
t-D.N.C. poll in partnership with Echelon Insights, showing that <b>Kamala<=
/b> <b>Harris</b>=E2=80=99s pivot to patriotism is resonating with voters, =
who now see the Democratic nominee as just as strong and tough as <b>Donald=
</b> <b>Trump</b>, even as the race remains tight. Still, our poll finds th=
at voters want to see <i>more</i> of Harris, and they really want her to st=
art talking to the media. It=E2=80=99s a juicy poll, so dig in=E2=80=94and =
stay =E2=80=99til the end for new data on whether voters have any idea what=
 all those =E2=80=9Cbrat=E2=80=9D memes actually
mean.<br/><br/><i>But first, here=E2=80=99s <b>Abby Livingston</b>=E2=80=99=
s roundup of the latest Capitol Hill chatter=E2=80=A6</i><br/></p>
          </td>
